      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical code verification benchmarks passed at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, pipe flow) were executed and results compared against analytical solutions. Errors within acceptable tolerances for MRL 2 classification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index) with GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA pump geometry. GCI values for the normalized index of hemolysis ranged from 1.8% to 3.4% across the five operating points, exceeding the Gradation 2 threshold and achieving Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable to CFD boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "PIV experimental conditions (fluid viscosity, inlet flow rate, rotational speed) are fully documented in the FDA benchmark dataset and match the CFD boundary conditions within measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined and applied to primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) was used as the primary comparison metric. RH values from CFD were within 12% of experimental measurements across all five operating points, satisfying Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly maps to clinical endpoint (hemolysis) and is justified for COU.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are established quantities for pump hemolysis assessment and are directly relevant to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry and operating conditions representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under operating conditions spanning the clinical CPB flow range (2–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM), directly representative of the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor category.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond code verification benchmarks is not required. Solver residuals were monitored to convergence (< 1e-5) for all simulations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2. Standard operating procedures were followed by experienced analysts."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Qualitative assessment of model form appropriateness documented with expert justification.",
      "rationale": "A qualitative assessment of model form adequacy was conducted by the credibility assessment team in consultation with subject-matter experts in computational hemodynamics. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance in rotating machinery flows with moderate adverse pressure gradients, which characterizes the impeller passage flow in centrifugal blood pumps. Literature evidence from at least six independent CFD studies of similar pump geometries supports the appropriateness of this turbulence closure for the flow regimes encountered across the five CPB operating points. The power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) was evaluated against alternative formulations (Heuser-Opitz, Zhang et al.) and found to produce consistent rank-ordering of hemolysis across operating conditions, which is the primary requirement for the worst-case identification objective of this COU. The team concluded that the selected model forms are appropriate and sufficient for the intended use, and this conclusion is documented in the credibility assessment report (CAR-2024-CPB-001). No structured gradation levels are assigned to this factor, as the assessment methodology applied is inherently qualitative and consensus-based, consistent with accepted practice for model form evaluation at this stage of device development."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. Nominal input values were taken from device specifications and clinical literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterization beyond what is documented in the FDA benchmark dataset is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between validation and COU contexts is implicitly addressed through the use of the FDA benchmark geometry and operating conditions. Formal assessment not required at MRL 2."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 is accepted at Model Risk Level 2. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; all seven achieved their required gradation levels (two factors exceeded requirements). Six factors were appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The model form factor was evaluated through a documented qualitative expert consensus process, with detailed justification provided in the rationale. Overall, the evidence base is sufficient to support the conclusion that the CFD model provides adequate credibility for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
